Inline Label Use Guide
======================

* * *
## API

### Configuration Options

When instantiating the `inline-label` app you may pass it an object as a parameter, the following are the possible attributes of this object:

<table class="api">
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>property</th>       <th>default value</th>      <th class="description">description</th>                <th>mandatory</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td>selector</td>       <td>null</td>               <td>CSS selector identifing: a form field (input:text
                                                                    or textarea) or a form, or any combination of form
                                                                    fields and forms</td>                               <td>TRUE</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>class_name</td>     <td>'inline-label'</td>     <td>class name applyed to the form fields affected by
                                                                    the `inline-label` app. As soon as you focus on the
                                                                    field and the `inlinelabel` is removed the class is
                                                                    also removed.</td>                                  <td>FALSE</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>remove_label</td>   <td>true</td>               <td>Flag indicating if the label should be removed if
                                                                    it is used as the `inlinelabel` of the field</td>     <td>FALSE</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>


* * *
## Styling

The class defined on the `class_name` when the `InlineLabel` is initialized (by default: `inline-label`) will be applied to any form field affected by this app if the field doesn't change the default value. e.g:

    .inline-label {
        color: #cccccc;
    }


* * *
## Customizing

If we pass `remove_label:false`, then the label will remain in the markup

    <label for="id_site_search" id="SearchLabel">Site Search</label>
    <input type="text" id="id_site_search" />
            
    <script type="text/javascript">
        //<![CDATA[
            new trapeze.InlineLabel({ selector: "#id_site_search2", remove_label:false});
        //]]>
    </script>
